DataElement.preferredName: Measurable Residual Disease Molecular Marker Type
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The type of molecular characteristics that are used as a biomarker for minimal residual disease.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Evidence for remaining tumor following primary treatment that is only apparent using highly sensitive techniques.:A characteristic that can be objectively measured and serves as an indicator for normal biologic processes, pathogenic processes, state of health or disease, the risk for disease development and/or prognosis, or responsiveness to a particular therapeutic intervention.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: remainder of a tumor or a neoplasm/cancer after primary, potentially curative therapy.

Concepts.definition: Evidence for remaining tumor following primary treatment that is only apparent using highly sensitive techniques.

Property.preferredDefinition: Objectively measurable phenotypic parameters (e.g., specific enzyme concentration, specific hormone concentration, specific gene phenotype, presence of biological substances) that characterize an organism's state of health or disease, likelihood of developing a disease, or response to a particular therapeutic intervention.

Concepts.definition: A characteristic that can be objectively measured and serves as an indicator for normal biologic processes, pathogenic processes, state of health or disease, the risk for disease development and/or prognosis, or responsiveness to a particular therapeutic intervention.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: Any specific activity undertaken during the course of a clinical study or research protocol.

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: A characteristic that can be objectively measured and serves as an indicator for normal biologic processes, pathogenic processes, state of health or disease, the risk for disease development and/or prognosis, or responsiveness to a particular therapeutic intervention._Something distinguishable as an identifiable class based on common qualities.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to a paracentric inversion involving breakpoints on the long (q23.1 and q26.2) of chromosome 3. It is associated with acute myeloid leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to a paracentric inversion involving breakpoints on the long (q23.1 and q26.2) of chromosome 3. It is associated with acute myeloid leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A change in the nucleotide sequence of the KRAS gene.

Concepts.definition: A change in the nucleotide sequence of the KRAS gene.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A chromosomal abnormality consisting of the translocation of genetic material from any one of several chromosomes to the 11q23.3 region, resulting in an MLL gene rearrangement.

Concepts.definition: A chromosomal abnormality consisting of the translocation of genetic material from any one of several chromosomes to the 11q23.3 region, resulting in an MLL gene rearrangement.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic aneuploidy abnormality that refers to the presence of one chromosome 5 only. It is associated with the development of refractory anemia with excess blasts, refractory anemia with multilineage dysplasia, and refractory anemia with multilineage dysplasia and ringed sideroblasts.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic aneuploidy abnormality that refers to the presence of one chromosome 5 only. It is associated with the development of refractory anemia with excess blasts, refractory anemia with multilineage dysplasia, and refractory anemia with multilineage dysplasia and ringed sideroblasts.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A chromosomal abnormality consisting of the absence of one of the copies of chromosome 7 in somatic cells.

Concepts.definition: A chromosomal abnormality consisting of the absence of one of the copies of chromosome 7 in somatic cells.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A change in the structure of the NRAS gene.

Concepts.definition: A change in the structure of the NRAS gene.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An indication that a cytogenetic rearrangement involving MLLT10 but not involving KMT2A was detected in a sample.

Concepts.definition: An indication that a cytogenetic rearrangement involving MLLT10 but not involving KMT2A was detected in a sample.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Mutation of the nucleophosmin gene. It is seen in acute myeloid leukemias usually associated with a normal karyotype.

Concepts.definition: Mutation of the nucleophosmin gene. It is seen in acute myeloid leukemias usually associated with a normal karyotype.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Mutation of the protein tyrosine phosphatase, non-receptor type 11 gene. It is seen in cases of juvenile myelomonocytic leukemia.

Concepts.definition: Mutation of the protein tyrosine phosphatase, non-receptor type 11 gene. It is seen in cases of juvenile myelomonocytic leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q21) of chromosome 1 and the long arm (q23) of chromosome 11. It is associated with KMT2A (MLL)/MLLT11 (AF1Q) fusions, acute myeloid leukemia and some cases of acute lymphoblastic leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q21) of chromosome 1 and the long arm (q23) of chromosome 11. It is associated with KMT2A (MLL)/MLLT11 (AF1Q) fusions, acute myeloid leukemia and some cases of acute lymphoblastic leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the short arm (p13.3) of chromosome 1 and the long arm (q13.1) of chromosome 22. It is associated with RBM15/MRTFA (MKL1) fusions and acute megakaryocytic leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the short arm (p13.3) of chromosome 1 and the long arm (q13.1) of chromosome 22. It is associated with RBM15/MRTFA (MKL1) fusions and acute megakaryocytic leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the short arm (p11.2) of chromosome 10 and the long arm (q23) of chromosome 11. It is associated with KMT2A (MLL)/ABI1 fusions and acute myeloid leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the short arm (p11.2) of chromosome 10 and the long arm (q23) of chromosome 11. It is associated with KMT2A (MLL)/ABI1 fusions and acute myeloid leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of chromosome 10p12 with chromosome 11q23. It is associated with acute myeloid leukemia in childhood.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of chromosome 10p12 with chromosome 11q23. It is associated with acute myeloid leukemia in childhood.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A change in the nucleotide sequence of the RUNX1 gene.

Concepts.definition: A change in the nucleotide sequence of the RUNX1 gene.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the allelic loss of all or part of the short arm of chromosome 17.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the loss of all or part of the short arm of chromosome 17 (17p).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to deletion of chromosome bands 31-32 on the long arm of chromosome 5.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to deletion of chromosome bands 31-32 on the long arm of chromosome 5.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality involving the rearrangement of two or more other chromosomes with the short arm of chromosome 12 (12p).

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality involving the rearrangement of two or more other chromosomes with the short arm of chromosome 12 (12p).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A genetic abnormality that arises from duplications of the juxtamembrane portion of the gene and results in constitutive activation of the FLT3 receptor tyrosine kinase protein in early hematopoietic progenitor cells. It is associated with acute myelogenous leukemia where it appears to correlate with a poor prognosis.

Concepts.definition: A genetic abnormality that arises from duplications of the juxtamembrane portion of the gene and results in constitutive activation of the FLT3 receptor tyrosine kinase protein in early hematopoietic progenitor cells. It is associated with acute myelogenous leukemia where it appears to correlate with a poor prognosis.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Single nucleotide mutations in the tyrosine kinase domain encoded by the human FLT3 gene that are associated with acute myeloid leukemia and poor prognosis.

Concepts.longName: FLT3 Tyrosine Kinase Domain Point Mutation
Concepts.definition: Single nucleotide mutations in the tyrosine kinase domain encoded by the human FLT3 gene that are associated with acute myeloid leukemia and poor prognosis.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A change in the nucleotide sequence of the GATA1 gene.

Concepts.definition: A change in the nucleotide sequence of the GATA1 gene.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A pericentric chromosomal inversion that involves chromosome 16. It is associated with CBFA2T3/GLIS2 fusions and pediatric acute megakaryoblastic leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A pericentric chromosomal inversion that involves chromosome 16. It is associated with CBFA2T3/GLIS2 fusions and pediatric acute megakaryoblastic leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A chromosomal inversion that involves chromosome 16. It is associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia CBFB-MYH11, acute myelomonocytic leukemia with abnormal eosinophils, and granulocytic sarcoma.

Concepts.definition: A chromosomal inversion that involves chromosome 16. It is associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia CBFB-MYH11, acute myelomonocytic leukemia with abnormal eosinophils, and granulocytic sarcoma.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A molecular abnormality indicating rearrangement of the MLL (KMT2A) gene.

Concepts.definition: A molecular abnormality indicating rearrangement of the KMT2A (MLL) gene.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The presence of mutations in both alleles of the CEBPA gene.

Concepts.definition: The presence of mutations in both alleles of the CEBPA gene.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The presence of mutations in only one allele of the CEBPA gene.

Concepts.definition: The presence of mutations in only one allele of the CEBPA gene.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Mutation of the CEBPA gene encoding CCAAT/enhancer binding protein alpha. It is seen in acute myeloid leukemias usually associated with a normal karyotype.

Concepts.definition: Mutation of the CEBPA gene encoding CCAAT/enhancer binding protein alpha. It is seen in acute myeloid leukemias usually associated with a normal karyotype.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A molecular genetic abnormality indicating the presence of a mutation in exon 17 of the KIT gene located within 4q11-q12.

Concepts.definition: A molecular genetic abnormality indicating the presence of a mutation in exon 17 of the KIT gene located within 4q11-q12.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A molecular genetic abnormality indicating the presence of a mutation in exon 8 of the KIT gene located within 4q11-q12.

Concepts.definition: A molecular genetic abnormality indicating the presence of a mutation in exon 8 of the KIT gene located within 4q11-q12.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A molecular genetic abnormality that refers to mutation of the c-kit (CD117) proto-oncogene. It is associated with the development of gastrointestinal stromal tumor and gastrointestinal autonomic nerve tumor. It has also been described in acute myeloid leukemias, dysgerminomas, and seminomas.

Concepts.definition: A molecular genetic abnormality that refers to mutation of the c-kit (CD117) proto-oncogene. It is associated with the development of gastrointestinal stromal tumor and gastrointestinal autonomic nerve tumor. It has also been described in acute myeloid leukemias, dysgerminomas, and seminomas.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to deletion of chromosome bands 14-21 on the long arm of chromosome 13.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to deletion of chromosome bands 14-21 on the long arm of chromosome 13.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q23) of chromosome 3 and the short arm (p12.3) of chromosome 12. It is associated with ETV6/MECOM (EVI1) fusions, myeloproliferative disorders, myelodysplastic syndromes and acute myelogenous leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q23) of chromosome 3 and the short arm (p12.3) of chromosome 12. It is associated with ETV6/MECOM (EVI1) fusions, myeloproliferative disorders, myelodysplastic syndromes and acute myelogenous leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation where both breakpoints are on the long arm (q23.1 and q26.2) of chromosome 3. It is associated with acute myeloid leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation where both breakpoints are on the long arm (q23.1 and q26.2) of chromosome 3. It is associated with acute myeloid leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q25) of chromosome 3 and the long arm (q34) of chromosome 5. It is associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia arising from myelodysplastic syndrome, acute myeloid leukemia with multilineage dysplasia, and acute myeloid leukemia with myelodysplasia-related changes.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q25) of chromosome 3 and the long arm (q34) of chromosome 5. It is associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia arising from myelodysplastic syndrome, acute myeloid leukemia with multilineage dysplasia, and acute myeloid leukemia with myelodysplasia-related changes.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A chromosomal abnormality consisting of the translocation of 4q21 with 11q23.

Concepts.definition: A chromosomal abnormality consisting of the translocation of 4q21 with 11q23.3.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of chromosome 11p15 with chromosome 5q35. It results in the formation of NUP98/NSD1 fusion gene. It is associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia with t(5;11)(q35;p15); NUP98-NSD1.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of chromosome 11p15 with chromosome 5q35. It results in the formation of NUP98/NSD1 fusion gene. It is associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia with t(5;11)(q35;p15); NUP98-NSD1.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q27) of chromosome 6 and the long arm (q23) of chromosome 11. It is associated with the development of de novo acute myeloid leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q27) of chromosome 6 and the long arm (q23) of chromosome 11. It is associated with the development of de novo acute myeloid leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the short arm (p23) of chromosome 6 and the long arm (q34.1) of chromosome 9. It is associated with DEK/NUP214 fusions, acute myeloid leukemia and myelodysplastic syndromes.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the short arm (p22.3) of chromosome 6 and the long arm (q34.1) of chromosome 9. It is associated with DEK/NUP214 fusions, acute myeloid leukemia and myelodysplastic syndromes.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the short arm (p11.2) of chromosome 8 and the short arm (p13.3) of chromosome 16. It is associated with KAT6A/CREBBP fusions and acute myeloid leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the short arm (p11.2) of chromosome 8 and the short arm (p13.3) of chromosome 16. It is associated with KAT6A/CREBBP fusions and acute myeloid leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the short arm (p21.3) of chromosome 9 and the long arm (q23.3) of chromosome 11. It is associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia with the MLLT3-MLL fusion gene transcript.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the short arm (p21.3) of chromosome 9 and the long arm (q23.3) of chromosome 11. It is associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia with the MLLT3-MLL fusion gene transcript.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A translocation between chromosomes 9 and 22 that is associated with the Philadelphia chromosome.

Concepts.definition: A translocation between chromosomes 9 and 22 that is associated with the Philadelphia chromosome.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A chromosomal abnormality consisting of the presence of a third copy of chromosome 8 in somatic cells.

Concepts.definition: A chromosomal abnormality consisting of the presence of a third copy of chromosome 8 in somatic cells.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A change in the nucleotide sequence of the WT1 gene.

Concepts.definition: A change in the nucleotide sequence of the WT1 gene.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned.

Concepts.definition: Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A chromosomal translocation involving the ETV6 gene on chromosome 12p13 and HLXB9 gene on chromosome 7q36.

Concepts.definition: A chromosomal translocation involving the ETV6 gene on chromosome 12p13 and HLXB9 gene on chromosome 7q36.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of chromosome 11p15 with chromosome 15q35. It results in the formation of NUP98/JARID1A fusion gene. It is associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia with t(11;15)(p15;q35); NUP98-JARID1A.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of chromosome 11p15 with chromosome 15q35. It results in the formation of NUP98/JARID1A fusion gene. It is associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia with t(11;15)(p15;q35); NUP98-JARID1A.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q23) of chromosome 11 and the long arm (q12-21) of chromosome 19. It is associated with KMT2A (MLL) fusions, including those with MLLT6 (AF17), and acute myeloid leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q23) of chromosome 11 and the long arm (q12-21) of chromosome 19. It is associated with KMT2A (MLL) fusions, including those with MLLT6 (AF17), and acute myeloid leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q23) of chromosome 11 and the short arm (p13.1) of chromosome 19. It is associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia with variant MLL translocations and topoisomerase II inhibitor-related acute myeloid leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q23.3) of chromosome 11 and the short arm (p13.1) of chromosome 19. It is associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia with variant MLL translocations and topoisomerase II inhibitor-related acute myeloid leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q23) of chromosome 11 and the short arm (p13) of chromosome 19. It is associated with KMT2A (MLL) fusions, including those with MLLT1 (ENL) and ELL, and acute myeloid leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q23) of chromosome 11 and the short arm (p13) of chromosome 19. It is associated with KMT2A (MLL) fusions, including those with MLLT1 (ENL) and ELL, and acute myeloid leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A chromosomal translocation associated with creation of a fusion between the PML and RARA genes. It is seen in variants of Acute Promyelocytic Leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A chromosomal translocation associated with creation of a fusion between the PML and RARA genes. It is seen in variants of acute promyelocytic leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A chromosomal translocation that involves chromosome 16. It is often associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia CBFB-MYH11, acute myelomonocytic leukemia with abnormal eosinophils, and granulocytic sarcoma.

Concepts.definition: A chromosomal translocation that involves chromosome 16. It is often associated with the development of acute myeloid leukemia CBFB-MYH11, acute myelomonocytic leukemia with abnormal eosinophils, and granulocytic sarcoma.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A chromosomal translocation involving the FUS gene on chromosome 16p11 and the ERG gene on chromosome 21q22.

Concepts.definition: A chromosomal translocation involving the FUS gene on chromosome 16p11 and the ERG gene on chromosome 21q22.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q24) of chromosome 16 and the long arm (q22) of chromosome 22. It is associated with RUNX1/CBFA2T3 fusions, myelodysplastic syndromes and acute myeloid leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q24) of chromosome 16 and the long arm (q22) of chromosome 22. It is associated with RUNX1/CBFA2T3 fusions, myelodysplastic syndromes and acute myeloid leukemia.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that involves a translocation between chromosomes 2 and 12.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that involves a translocation between chromosomes 2 and 12.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q23.3) of chromosome 11 and the short arm (p13.3) of chromosome 19 and . It is associated with KMT2A (MLL)/MLLT10 fusions and acute myeloid leukemia.

Concepts.definition: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the long arm (q23.3) of chromosome 11 and the short arm (p13.3) of chromosome 19. It is associated with KMT2A (MLL)/MLLT1 (ENL) fusions and acute myeloid leukemia.
